===Etymology===
{{calque|en|NL.|Achillis tendo}}, a term devised by the Dutch anatomist {{w|Philip Verheyden}} in 1693 in reference to the mythological account of [[Achilles]] being held by the heel when dipped in the {{w|Styx|River Styx}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|anatomy}} The strong [[tendon]] formed of the united tendons of the large [[muscle]]s in the [[calf]] of the leg, and inserted into the bone of the heel.

